tb-Pp7HvS2_gtL2qXvju2yc8kQyZxGIYLPlLm4DwLj3oRRPoafqJUYaC2XbHudVb5tcOlOr3EBQxu459IkifHB1klGaDzSSrC6BQjfQt4NmKhg9TcqbklHp9InbVoc91IwG0w9cKfA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering record creation**\\n\\nI need to batch-create records with timestamps in milliseconds, and while 29 records feel a bit lengthy, it seems manageable. Using Python could simplify crafting the JSON payload from search results. Maybe I could directly call the tool since we already have results. However, if local transformations aren't useful, maybe I should just focus on fewer records. It looks like using ISO strings might be easier, but the user has requested a bitable format, so I will stick to that!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Simplifying record creation**\\n\\nI’m thinking of using exec to convert all ISO strings from the search output if I paste a compact JSON list. This could help in outputting the records as a JSON snippet. I still need to call the tool with an object from the results, and I’m considering crafting 29 records manually, potentially omitting timestamps. While date fields might be optional, they'll still be useful. To simplify, I can focus on title, link, document type, and owner/editor. I’ll leave timestamps blank since the schema has those fields. Let’s go with 29 records without timestamps!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_j6fuja3MsbI01aV3qzbCbhor|fc_0ca5b223d5a1af220169b19b730a84819198b09c2dabb112e2","name":"feishu_bitable_app_table_record","arguments":{"action":"batch_create","app_token":"LiULbGl5BaA7Mes1Tehc4fXqnsd","table_id":"tbljg74YKZs30P80","records":[{"fields":{"标题":"重要文章沉淀库","链接":{"text":"打开","link":"https://pugmarp5va.feishu.cn/base/G1AAbhetoaOFxfsZVnUcqfv5nmc"},"文档类型":"多维表格","内容分类":"系统数据表","交互判定":"高概率是","判定依据":"刚由本次对话创建，用于重要文章沉淀。","所有者":"苏传磊","最近编辑人":"苏传磊"}},{"fields":{"标题":"文章拆解｜新手必看的11个 OpenClaw 实战案例","链接":{"text":"打开","link":"https://pugmarp5va.feishu.cn/docx/HkzjdxdCPoH9UqxWWLJctTzqnyd"},"文档类型":"文档","内容分类":"文