{"type":"message","id":"6ac108f3","parentId":"ac4bda9d","timestamp":"2026-03-11T16:47:07.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Updating records and tables**\n\nI need to update around 29 records, perhaps using a batch update method with the right keywords and stage. I’m considering creating sub-tables for each content classification, around eight in total. Using batch creation for each table makes sense. I should also update the total table with created and updated times, as well as inferred keywords. While automatic fields are available, it might be better to create user-defined explicit date fields for accuracy. It feels a bit tedious to handle all these mappings, but I'll get through it.\n\n**Creating tables from search results**\n\nI’m considering using existing search results with manual mapping only for high-probability entries, but the user wants to fill in some fields on the total table. Should I add document creation and update metadata from the outputs? It feels a bit overwhelming with 29 records, but I think I can manage it. I need to create tables by content categories such as system data, article breakdowns, diaries, references, projects, broadcasts, research papers, and presentations. Let’s go ahead and create those batch tables!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_0ca5b223d5a1af220169b19c80c0688191bba73b7815644432\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsZyLYDcroet0ZUaoXr-_Ge7a8ZrgVAitpWckHnjbxtcdg3hbhgMpyuR2IcRN1xOiJXRIKF9o1Slc5at_iTFBroE3XMEEczay6L6PvS2yozNNbg4RkCDV-VFJYF_v1Nqv8Ly4-CUFBSQSHUuEmjfDRlYD1s2kNib3LU7WWIUV69iMGOFW8oRdwL45SwGGq4dCz1dAJp76mdrNQdeWHzlRBjyQu6LrEDcInRlhqO3R9NFNMZXdr6oNgx6AEjt3o2zmBoVRG1xi-EpNwra1RvGLwxP4RO2eUtuF1h64FDgGJlcYE8A0y9sd9hOVuWhsq-9-w-lx1Ntdtf_pEo9Umo798LCN3NpAGVNAW6oRANLnkz2EIxs-umBONPNYGKLqnCnu5j9zlqmPa_zCIR0yV9E5J5d7tMPkHdM7SM1lozSiXk7MemimYDmUETTbvzVBjxN0ESdSmO-YeFIckaLCyFLfGMgkBFCloFj5_64DB3HmqltduCVDYcSB7km8ZFsiLHFPXr1pjrcQgOS7VZ5PusKC0nHBs0nChqXhJ4JFWiR